  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empower 30 Refugee Women In Leros Through Sewing</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Advocacy Project (AP) is launching this campaign to help Sewing 4 Solidarity, an inspiring voluntary initiative on the Greek Island of Leros, to train 30 refugee and migrant women in making handbags. Most of the women have fled war in the Middle East, and they are deeply uncertain about what lies ahead. The campaign will help them to draw comfort from working together and fortify them for the future. The campaign will also build trust between the refugees and local residents on Leros.</narrative>
  </description>
